explanation: Uses two stacks (in and out). Elements are pushed onto 'in'. When pop/peek is called, elements are moved from 'in' to 'out' only when 'out' is empty, reversing the order to achieve FIFO. Each element is moved at most once, giving amortized O(1) time.

